The paper presents a technique for trajectory synthesis for autonomous mobile robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach uses expected information density maps, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of a robotic electrolocation platform for target estimation suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG).
